<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 28 at 3:16PM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of central Meagher
County through 345 PM MDT...
At 315 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles west of White Sulphur Springs, moving east at 10 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph, pea size hail and localized
heavy downpours.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of central Meagher
County.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
